    <remarks>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.ScrollBarState" /> values correspond to the states of the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement" /> objects exposed by the following classes:</para>
      <list type="bullet">
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.LeftTrackHorizontal" />
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.RightTrackHorizontal" />
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.LowerTrackVertical" />
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.UpperTrackVertical" />
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.ThumbButtonHorizontal" />
          </para>
        </item>
        <item>
          <para>
            <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.VisualStyleElement.ScrollBar.ThumbButtonVertical" />
          </para>
        </item>
      </list>
      <para>The <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.VisualStyles.ScrollBarState" /> values are also used as an argument in the <see cref="T:System.Windows.Forms.ScrollBarRenderer" /> class methods that draw the scroll bar track, scroll box (also known as the thumb), and scroll box grip.</para>
    </remarks>
    <summary>
      <attribution license="cc4" from="Microsoft" modified="false" />
      <para>Specifies the visual state of a scroll bar that is drawn with visual styles.</para>
    </summary>
  </Docs>
